  heroImg={heroImg}
  overviewTitle="Stop grinding. Protect your enamel."
  overviewText="Bruxism is a parafunctional habit — meaning it occurs outside normal jaw function, typically during sleep, and usually unconsciously. The grinding and clenching forces involved can exceed normal chewing forces by two to three times, which is why bruxism causes such rapid wear. Over time it flattens the biting edges of front teeth, chips the cusps of back teeth, cracks existing restorations, and strains the temporomandibular joint (TMJ). A custom nightguard interposes a protective barrier between your upper and lower teeth, absorbing those forces before they damage enamel."
  overviewExtra="Many patients in Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck come to Thrive Dental with worn teeth, cracked restorations, or morning jaw soreness — and are surprised to learn that bruxism is the cause. We detect grinding wear at every comprehensive exam, often before patients are even aware they're doing it. Our custom nightguards are fabricated from a precise digital impression of your teeth, making them thinner and more accurately fitted than anything available over the counter. Unlike bulky drugstore guards that many patients remove during sleep without realizing it, a well-fitting custom guard stays in place all night. If you grind, a nightguard is the single most cost-effective thing you can do to preserve your dental work and avoid crowns, replacements, and jaw pain down the road."
